places.perex: Although this ZOO and botanical garden seems to be on the small side, you will be surprised by the variety of animals and plants.

places.name: Mansourah Beach
places.perex: This splendid natural beach is family-friendly. It also caters to the sport lovers.

places.name: Sidi Mansour Beach
places.perex: A lovely beach with fine white sand and clear sea. Popular with the holidaymakers, so there are plenty of amenities.

places.name: Kerkennah Islands
places.perex: This cluster of islands is a favourite holiday destination of Tunisians and no wonder why - secluded, paradise-like beaches and untouched…

places.name: Dar Essid Museum
places.perex: This museum situated in a residential house illustrates the living conditions of well-to-do Tunisians in the 18th century.

places.name: Lalla Hadria Museum
places.perex: This museum is dedicated to the marvels of Islamic art. Impressive collection of mosaics, ornamentally decorated artefacts and items of…

places.name: Ksar Ouled Soltane
places.perex: A fortified bunker atop the hill was built by Berbers in the 15th century. The Mos Espa scenes from SW: The Phantom Menace were filmed there.

places.name: Dar Alloch Beach
places.perex: This beach has a lot to offer: fine white sand, mild sea and various facilities. Awarded with Blue Flag.

places.name: Chott el Gharsa
places.perex: Every fan of Star Wars should visit these two ghost towns that have been built for the purpose of Episode I filming.
